condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :MOU between ADI and IIA, Schedule 2, Section I, A, 8 (b) | Description :The Borrower shall, not later than sixmonths after the Effective Date ensure that a memorandum of understanding for the implementation of subcomponent 1.3 of the Projecthas been executed on behalf of ADI and Institute of Agricultural Research (Institute de Investigacao Agraria, IIA), in form andsubstance acceptable to the Bank. | Due Date :05-Apr-2017

Finance Agreement :Mid-Term Review, Schedule 2, Section II, C, 1 (a) | Description :The Borrower shall no later than twenty-fourmonths after the Effective Date, carry out jointly with the Bank a mid-term review of the progress made in carrying out theProject. As part of the midterm review, the Borrower and the Bank shall review a report prepared and submitted by the PIU threemonths in advance of the mid-term review. | Due Date :05-Oct-2018

Finance Agreement :Project Coordination Committee, Schedule 2, Section I, A, 2 (a) | Description :The Borrower, through itsMinistry of Agriculture, shall establish, not later than six months after the Effective Date, and thereafter maintain, throughoutthe implementation of the Project, a coordination committee (Project Coordination Committee or PCC), with a composition, mandate,and resources satisfactory to the Bank, and which shall be chaired by the Minister of Agriculture. | Due Date :05-Apr-2017

Finance Agreement :Project Implementation Sub-Committee, Schedule 2, Section I, A, 3 (a) | Description :The Borrower shallestablish, not later than six months after the Effective Date and thereafter maintain, throughout the implementation of theProject, an implementation sub-committee (Project Implementation Sub-Committee or PISC) under the PCC, with a composition, mandate,and resources satisfactory to the Bank. | Due Date :05-Apr-2017

Finance Agreement :Project Implementation Unit, Schedule 2, Section I, A, 4 (a) | Description :The Borrower shall establish, notlater than six months after the Effective Date, and thereafter maintain, throughout the implementation of the Project, a projectimplementation unit (Project Implementation Unit or PIU) within the Agriculture Development Institute (ADI), with functions,staffing and resources satisfactory to the Bank. | Due Date :05-Apr-2017

Finance Agreement :Provincial Project Coordination Committees, Schedule 2, Section I, A, 5 (a) | Description :The Borrower shallestablish, not later than six months after the Effective Date, and thereafter maintain, throughout the implementation of theProject, a provincial coordination committee for each of the Participating Provinces (Provincial Project Coordination Committee orPPCC), with a composition, mandate, and resources satisfactory to the Bank. Each PPCC shall be chaired by the provincialvice-governor responsible for economic development of the corresponding participating province. | Due Date :05-Apr-2017

Finance Agreement :Provincial Project Coordination Sub-Committees, Schedule 2, Section I, A, 6 (a) | Description :The Borrowershall establish, not later than six months after the Effective Date, and thereafter maintain, throughout the implementation of theProject, a provincial implementation sub-committee for each of the participating provinces (Provincial Project ImplementationSub-Committee or PPISC) under the corresponding PPCC, with a composition, mandate, and resources satisfactory to the Bank. | DueDate :05-Apr-2017

Finance Agreement :Provincial Project Implementation Units, Schedule 2, Section I, A, 7 (a) | Description :The Borrower shallestablish, not later than six months after the Effective Date, and thereafter maintain, throughout the implementation of theProject, a provincial project implementation unit for each of the participating provinces (Provincial Project Implementation Unitor PPIU) within the corresponding provincial offices of ADI, with functions, staffing and resources satisfactory to the Bank. | DueDate :05-Apr-2017

Finance Agreement :Recruitment of Certain Personnel for each PPIU, Schedule 2, Section I, A, 7 (c) | Description :The Borrowershall recruit for each PPIU, not later than three months after the Effective Date, a provincial project coordinator, accountant,and monitoring and evaluation specialist, each with qualifications, experience and terms of reference acceptable to the Bank, andin accordance with the provisions of Section III of Schedule 2 to of the Legal Agreement. | Due Date :05-Jan-2017

Finance Agreement :Recruitment of External Auditor, Schedule 2, Section II, B, 5 | Description :The Borrower shall recruit, notlater than six months after the Effective Date, an external auditor with qualifications, experience and terms of referencesatisfactory to the Bank, in accordance with the provisions of Section III of Schedule 2 of the Loan Agreement. | Due Date:05-Apr-2017

Finance Agreement :Recruitment of a Service Provider, Schedule 2, Section I, A, 8 (a) | Description :The Borrower shall, not laterthan six months after the Effective Date hire a service provider to assist in the implementation of Part B of the Project, withqualifications, experience and terms of reference acceptable to the Bank, and in accordance with the provisions of Section III ofSchedule 2 of the Legal Agreement. | Due Date :05-Apr-2017

Finance Agreement :Updating the Financial Managment and Accounting System, Schedule 2, Section II, | Description :The Borrowershall update, not later than three months after Effective Date, its financial management and accounting system to incorporate theProject. | Due Date :05-Jan-2017
